<h1> How to be a responsible reportive journalist</h1>
  <h3> In this blurb I will be teaching you how to be resposible on your jounrey through your career in journalism career  </h3> 
  
  <h2> Be timely </h2>
  <p> The first thing you should consider when creating a newstory is if it is timely. 
  This means that your topic is not only fresh, but it has not been recently over covered. <br> It is important to be timely as to make sure that you are reporting imoportant current events. </p>
  <h2> Report on newsworthy topics </h2>
  <p> When you are writing your story stop and think, is this something that I would want to read about? 
  You must consider if what you are writing about is something that your audience wants to hear about. This
  also brings up the idea of making sure you report proper topics to proper audiences. </p>
  <h2> Give credit where credit is due </h2>
  <p> In any form of media you post, you must remember to credit your sources.
  Giving credit to the orginial source of you information is important as to not break any laws.
  It is important to show that your information is from reliable sources. </p>  
  <h2> Don't spread false information </h2>
  <p> One of the most important rules in being a journalist is to not spread false information. 
  It is important to maintain your integrity as a journalist. Make sure you double check your sources, and 
  confrim that the information you are puttinng out is correct. </p>
  <h2> Double check your information </h2>
  <p> As stated before it is important to make sure tha your information is correct. Focus on double checking 
  your source. Along with this, try to look at multiple sources to see if the information you are tryign to report
  is the same across all of the sources. 
  <h2> Look for the small details </h2>
  <p> Lastly it is important to look out for small details in your story. There are always going to be multiple
  reporters who are reporting the same story as you. If you want to stand out, focus on looking for the small 
  details in a story. </p>
